<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>G-Transcriber Pipeline Report</title>
    {% if plotly_js %}
    <script>{{ plotly_js | safe }}</script>
    {% else %}
    <script src="https://cdn.plot.ly/plotly-latest.min.js"></script>
    {% endif %}
    <style>
    {% include '_styles.css' %}
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>G-Transcriber Pipeline Report</h1>
    <p class="report-subtitle">
        Cognitive Elicitation Pipeline &mdash; Interactive results dashboard for transcription
        processing, Bloom-scaffolded QA generation, and LLM-as-a-Judge validation.
        Use the filters below to segment data by pipeline run, location, participant,
        confidence threshold, or Bloom taxonomy level. All charts update in real time.
    </p>

    <!-- Global Filter Bar -->
    <div id="filter-bar">
        <div class="filter-group">
            <label for="filter-pipeline">Pipeline</label>
            <select id="filter-pipeline" multiple></select>
        </div>
        <div class="filter-group">
            <label for="filter-location">Location</label>
            <select id="filter-location" multiple></select>
        </div>
        <div class="filter-group">
            <label for="filter-participant">Participant</label>
            <select id="filter-participant" multiple></select>
        </div>
        <div class="filter-group">
            <label>Min Confidence</label>
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;">
                <input type="range" id="filter-confidence" min="0" max="1" step="0.05" value="0">
                <span id="confidence-value">0.00</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="filter-group">
            <label>Bloom Levels</label>
            <div id="filter-bloom" class="bloom-toggles"></div>
        </div>
        <button id="btn-reset-filters">Reset</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Summary Stat Cards -->
    <div id="summary-cards">
        <div class="stat-card">
            <h3>Total Runs</h3>
            <div class="value" id="card-total-runs">0</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
            <h3>Transcriptions</h3>
            <div class="value" id="card-total-transcriptions">0</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
            <h3>QA Pairs</h3>
            <div class="value" id="card-total-qa">0</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
            <h3>Avg Success Rate</h3>
            <div class="value" id="card-avg-success">N/A</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
            <h3>QA Validity Rate</h3>
            <div class="value" id="card-valid-rate">N/A</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
            <h3>Avg Validation Score</h3>
            <div class="value" id="card-avg-score">N/A</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Tab Navigation -->
    <nav id="tab-nav">
        <button data-tab="overview" class="active">Overview</button>
        <button data-tab="qa">QA Analysis</button>
        <button data-tab="transcriptions">Transcriptions</button>
        <button data-tab="source">Source Data</button>
        <button data-tab="compare">Compare Runs</button>
    </nav>

    <!-- ==================== Overview Tab ==================== -->
    <div id="tab-overview" class="tab-panel active">
        <h2 class="section-title">Pipeline Run Summary</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">
            Overview of all pipeline runs discovered in the results directory.
            Each row shows the pipeline ID, which processing steps were executed,
            completion status, wall-clock duration, overall success rate, and
            the number of items processed.
        </p>
        <div id="chart-run-summary-table"></div>

        <div class="chart-row">
            <div class="chart-container">
                <h3 class="chart-title">Success Rate &amp; Duration</h3>
                <p class="chart-desc">
                    Per-run success rate (percentage of items processed without errors)
                    and total wall-clock processing duration in seconds. Helps identify
                    runs with anomalous failure rates or processing bottlenecks.
                </p>
                <div id="chart-pipeline-overview"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="chart-container">
                <h3 class="chart-title">Run Timeline</h3>
                <p class="chart-desc">
                    Chronological progression of pipeline runs. Each marker represents a
                    run plotted by creation date (x-axis) and success rate (y-axis).
                    Marker size is proportional to the number of items processed.
                </p>
                <div id="chart-run-timeline"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ==================== QA Analysis Tab ==================== -->
    <div id="tab-qa" class="tab-panel">
        <h2 class="section-title">QA Pair Analysis</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">
            Analysis of Bloom-scaffolded question-answer pairs generated by the
            Cognitive Elicitation Pipeline (CEP). Includes Bloom taxonomy distribution,
            LLM-as-a-Judge validation score distributions, inter-criterion correlations,
            and multi-dimensional quality profiling.
        </p>

        <div class="chart-row">
            <div class="chart-container">
                <h3 class="chart-title">Bloom Taxonomy Distribution</h3>
                <p class="chart-desc">
                    Stacked bar chart showing the count of QA pairs at each Bloom
                    cognitive level (Remember, Understand, Analyze, Evaluate) per
                    pipeline run. Reveals the cognitive diversity of the generated dataset.
                </p>
                <div id="chart-bloom-distribution"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="chart-container">
                <h3 class="chart-title">Validation Score Distributions</h3>
                <p class="chart-desc">
                    Violin plots of the four LLM-as-a-Judge validation criteria:
                    <strong>Faithfulness</strong> (grounding in context),
                    <strong>Bloom Calibration</strong> (cognitive level accuracy),
                    <strong>Informativeness</strong> (tacit knowledge elicitation), and
                    <strong>Self-Containedness</strong> (question independence from context).
                    Violins reveal bimodal distributions that box plots would hide.
                </p>
                <div id="chart-validation-violins"></div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chart-row">
            <div class="chart-container">
                <h3 class="chart-title">Bloom Level &times; Validation Criterion Heatmap</h3>
                <p class="chart-desc">
                    Mean validation score for each combination of Bloom taxonomy level
                    (rows) and validation criterion (columns). Cells are annotated with
                    mean &plusmn; standard deviation. Identifies which cognitive levels
                    are hardest to validate (e.g., higher-order levels may have lower
                    Bloom calibration scores).
                </p>
                <div id="chart-bloom-validation-heatmap"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="chart-container">
                <h3 class="chart-title">Confidence Score Distribution</h3>
                <p class="chart-desc">
                    Histogram of LLM generation confidence scores across all QA pairs.
                    High-confidence clusters suggest the model found clear extractive
                    grounding; low-confidence tails may indicate speculative or
                    weakly-supported answers.
                </p>
                <div id="chart-confidence-distribution"></div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chart-row">
            <div class="chart-container">
                <h3 class="chart-title">Multi-hop vs Single-hop Questions</h3>
                <p class="chart-desc">
                    Proportion of QA pairs requiring multi-hop reasoning (connecting
                    distant text segments) versus single-hop extraction. Multi-hop
                    questions are more challenging for downstream KG-based QA systems.
                </p>
                <div id="chart-multihop"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="chart-container">
                <h3 class="chart-title">Validation Criteria Correlation Matrix</h3>
                <p class="chart-desc">
                    Pearson correlation coefficients between the four validation criteria
                    and generation confidence. Strong positive correlations suggest
                    redundant criteria; negative correlations reveal trade-offs
                    (e.g., informativeness may inversely correlate with faithfulness
                    for tacit knowledge questions).
                </p>
                <div id="chart-correlation-heatmap"></div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chart-container">
            <h3 class="chart-title">Parallel Coordinates: Multi-dimensional Quality Profile</h3>
            <p class="chart-desc">
                Each line represents a single QA pair, plotted across five quality
                dimensions (confidence, faithfulness, Bloom calibration, informativeness,
                self-containedness). Lines are colored by Bloom taxonomy level.
                Patterns of parallel lines reveal quality clusters; crossing lines
                indicate trade-offs between dimensions.
            </p>
            <div id="chart-parallel-coordinates"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ==================== Transcriptions Tab ==================== -->
    <div id="tab-transcriptions" class="tab-panel">
        <h2 class="section-title">Transcription Quality</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">
            Quality metrics for ASR transcription outputs. The quality checker evaluates
            script match (expected language usage), repetition artifacts, segment boundary
            quality, and content density. The radar chart compares aggregate quality
            profiles across pipeline runs.
        </p>

        <div class="chart-container">
            <h3 class="chart-title">Transcription Quality Score Distributions</h3>
            <p class="chart-desc">
                Histograms for five quality sub-scores: <strong>Overall</strong> (composite),
                <strong>Script Match</strong> (correct language/script detection),
                <strong>Repetition</strong> (absence of repeated segments),
                <strong>Segment Quality</strong> (clean timestamp boundaries), and
                <strong>Content Density</strong> (information per unit length).
                The sixth panel shows the validity rate (pass/fail against the quality threshold).
            </p>
            <div id="chart-transcription-quality"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="chart-container">
            <h3 class="chart-title">Quality Radar: Mean Scores by Run</h3>
            <p class="chart-desc">
                Radar (spider) chart comparing mean validation criterion scores and
                mean transcription quality across pipeline runs. Each polygon represents
                one run; larger area indicates higher overall quality. Useful for
                identifying runs with specific quality deficiencies.
            </p>
            <div id="chart-quality-radar"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ==================== Source Data Tab ==================== -->
    <div id="tab-source" class="tab-panel">
        <h2 class="section-title">Source Data Provenance</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">
            Metadata from the original interview recordings: participant identity,
            geographic location, recording date. This section helps assess coverage
            across the research population and identify potential geographic or
            participant-level biases in the generated dataset.
        </p>

        <div class="chart-row">
            <div class="chart-container">
                <h3 class="chart-title">Location &gt; Participant Hierarchy</h3>
                <p class="chart-desc">
                    Treemap showing the hierarchical breakdown of source documents by
                    recording location and participant name. Tile area is proportional
                    to the number of documents. Reveals geographic concentration and
                    participant representation balance.
                </p>
                <div id="chart-location-treemap"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="chart-container">
                <h3 class="chart-title">Participant Breakdown</h3>
                <p class="chart-desc">
                    Grouped bar chart showing the number of source documents and
                    generated QA pairs per participant. Large discrepancies between
                    document count and QA pair count may indicate variable content
                    richness across interviews.
                </p>
                <div id="chart-participant-breakdown"></div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chart-container">
            <h3 class="chart-title">Validation Scores by Location</h3>
            <p class="chart-desc">
                Violin plots of overall validation scores grouped by recording location.
                Differences across locations may reflect variation in interview content
                richness, transcription quality, or tacit knowledge density.
            </p>
            <div id="chart-location-quality"></div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="chart-title" style="margin-top:24px;">Document-Level Detail</h3>
        <p class="chart-desc">
            Expandable table listing every source document with its metadata, QA pair
            count, mean validation score, and Bloom level distribution (shown as inline
            color bars). Click a row to expand and inspect individual QA pairs with
            their per-criterion scores.
        </p>
        <div id="chart-document-table"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- ==================== Compare Runs Tab ==================== -->
    <div id="tab-compare" class="tab-panel">
        <h2 class="section-title">Cross-Run Comparison</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">
            Side-by-side comparison of two pipeline runs. Select runs from the dropdowns
            below and click <strong>Compare</strong> to generate overlapping violin plots
            for each validation criterion and a radar chart comparing mean quality profiles.
            Useful for evaluating the impact of model changes, prompt tuning, or
            configuration adjustments between runs.
        </p>

        <div id="compare-controls">
            <label for="compare-run-a">Run A:</label>
            <select id="compare-run-a"></select>
            <label for="compare-run-b">Run B:</label>
            <select id="compare-run-b"></select>
            <button id="btn-compare">Compare</button>
        </div>

        <div class="chart-container">
            <h3 class="chart-title">Validation Score Comparison (Violin Plots)</h3>
            <p class="chart-desc">
                Overlapping violin plots for each validation criterion, comparing the
                selected runs. Distribution shape differences reveal systematic quality
                shifts between runs.
            </p>
            <div id="chart-cross-run-comparison"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="chart-container">
            <h3 class="chart-title">Quality Radar Comparison</h3>
            <p class="chart-desc">
                Radar chart comparing mean scores across the four validation criteria
                and transcription quality for the two selected runs. Overlapping
                polygons highlight dimensions where one run outperforms the other.
            </p>
            <div id="chart-compare-radar"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <footer>
        <p>Generated by G-Transcriber Report Generator | {{ timestamp }}</p>
    </footer>

    <!-- Embedded Dataset -->
    <script>window.__REPORT_DATA__ = {{ dataset_json | tojson }};</script>

    <!-- Filter Engine + Chart Builders -->
    <script>
    {% include '_filter_engine.js' %}
    </script>
</body>
</html>
